    <title>Morse resolutions of powers of square-free monomial ideals of projective
  dimension one</title>
    <summary>  Let $I$ be a square-free monomial ideal $I$ of projective dimension one.
Starting with the Taylor complex on the generators of $I^r$, we use Discrete
Morse theory to describe a CW complex that supports a minimal free resolution
of $I^r$. To do so, we concretely describe the acyclic matching on the faces of
the Taylor complex.
</summary>
